      "writtenOn": "2020-07-02T03:40:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general, these to names don\u0027t seem to suit what they do. The \u0027get\u0027 implies some form of idempotent behavior, that if one calls this with a given nodeId at one point and then calls it with the same nodeId later that the same value will be returned. But these actually always create a new markId / parentTreeId (actually a structParentId?). They should either be renamed \u0027createNew*\u0027 instead of \u0027get*\u0027 to eliminate the confusion, or they should be modified to actually be getters (which may create a new id if not already present, but that would be opaque to the caller).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 0,
